o-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 22, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104api1665703054623.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/api1665703054623.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/api1665703054623.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"api1665703054623\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies the font size that determines the size of the <dfn class=\"term\">character cell</dfn>, a\n      unit of measurement that is used by Uniface to control the size and placement of forms and\n      fields in Windows and character mode applications.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"api1665703054623__topic_d145814e1_d145815e1_d145816e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"api1665703054623__p_d145817e1_d145818e1_d145819e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Font0</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=\"</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Font</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Size</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Stye</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"api1665703054623__section_w3290ab1b5b3_w3291ab1b5_w3292ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"api1665703054623__table_d17783e1_d17784e1_d17785e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"Courier\n                           New,Western,9,regular\"</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">File section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wyv1665702675417.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyv1665702675417.html\" title=\"The [screen] section of the initialization file defines the fonts used in the GUI user interface and additional settings for screen display.\">[screen]</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"api1665703054623__section_iyj_ttw_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1147677e124\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The layout of a form, is based on a grid of character cells, and the size of each cell\n            is based on <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Font0</span>. A character cell is equivalent to the space\n            occupied by one character on the screen in character mode.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The form size is defined in character cells, so a form of 35x85 is 35 character cells\n            high and 85 cells wide.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Character cells also provide the coordinates for placing objects such as entities,\n            labels, and fields on a form and setting the length of widgets.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The form window property <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Cell Height</span> can be used to scale the\n            grid to be larger or smaller. It can be set in the application initialization file, or\n            in the individual forms. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hwg1665702769717.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hwg1665702769717.html\" title=\"Window property that defines the size of the virtual grid used in the form layout, expressed as a percentage of Font0. The grid is used when defining the form dimensions and the size and position of objects in the form layout.\">Cell Height (CellHeight)</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525816\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525816\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Font0 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 22, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifies the font size that determines the size of the character cell , a unit of measurement that is used by Uniface to control the size and placement of forms and fields in Windows and character mode applications. Font0 =\" Font , Size , Stye \" Default value \"Courier New,Western,9,regular\" File section [screen] Description The layout of a form, is based on a grid of character cells, and the size of each cell is based on Font0 . A character cell is equivalent to the space occupied by one character on the screen in character mode. The form size is defined in character cells, so a form of 35x85 is 35 character cells high and 85 cells wide. Character cells also provide the coordinates for placing objects such as entities, labels, and fields on a form and setting the length of widgets. The form window property Cell Height can be used to scale the grid to be larger or smaller. It can be set in the application initialization file, or in the individual forms. For more information, see Cell Height (CellHeight) . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}